---
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="DS-V2 components, Jeff Mills"
  description="Architectural overview of the DS-V2 component library: a Vue 3 source layer that compiles to standards-based custom elements, backed by a reactive composables layer for shadow-DOM-aware primitives."
>
  <p class="project-back"><a href="/projects/design-system-v2">&laquo; back to ds-v2</a></p>
  <h1 class="page-title">ds-v2 · component library</h1>
  <p class="project-meta">
    <span class="project-year">2020-2025</span>
    <span class="meta-sep">&middot;</span>
    <span class="project-status">proprietary</span>
    <span class="meta-sep">&middot;</span>
    <span>~70 components</span>
    <span class="meta-sep">&middot;</span>
    <span>vue 3 + composition api</span>
  </p>

  <p class="page-lede">
    Two parallel layers, plus the reactive primitives underneath. The Vue 3
    single-file components are the canonical source; the custom elements
    are the compiled output, registered via <code>defineCustomElement</code>
    so any framework or no framework can consume them.
  </p>

  <aside class="callout">
    <span class="callout-label">Architectural overview only</span>
    <p>
      Component source stays in the private repository. The patterns and
      architecture are described below. Happy to walk through component
      implementations under NDA,
      <a href="mailto:jeffy9@gmail.com">reach out</a>.
    </p>
  </aside>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <h2 class="section-title">the three layers</h2>

  <dl class="stack-list">
    <dt>vue source layer</dt>
    <dd>
      Roughly 70 Vue 3 single-file components, the canonical source.
      Coverage spans forms, charts, modals, navigation, layouts, content,
      and media. Each component is a TypeScript <code>setup</code> script
      with a typed <code>Props</code> interface and TSDoc on every prop.
    </dd>
    <dt>custom-elements layer</dt>
    <dd>
      Roughly 60 custom elements, the compiled output. Each one wraps a
      Vue SFC via <code>defineCustomElement</code> and registers it with
      the global registry. Framework-agnostic consumers use these tags
      directly.
    </dd>
    <dt>composables</dt>
    <dd>
      Roughly a dozen reactive primitives the components compose with.
      Shadow-DOM-aware host bindings, slotted-descendant lookups,
      reactive attribute binding, viewport, resize, click-outside, DOM
      element handles by id, an HTTP request hook. Vue 3 Composition
      API throughout, no mixins.
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <h2 class="section-title">patterns you'll see across the library</h2>
  <ul class="proof-list">
    <li>
      <strong>TypeScript <code>Props</code> interfaces with TSDoc.</strong>
      Drives both the component API and the build-time IDE metadata
      generator. One source of truth for prop types, descriptions, and
      defaults. The same metadata feeds the MCP server downstream.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Composables, not mixins.</strong> Vue 3 Composition API
      throughout. The reactive primitives, shadow-DOM-aware host
      bindings, slotted-descendant lookups, viewport, resize,
      click-outside, are factored into a small, testable composables
      layer that the components compose with.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Shadow DOM-safe by default.</strong> Components ship with
      shadow DOM enabled; tokens propagate via CSS custom properties so
      theming pierces the boundary without the component needing to know.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Cross-element reactive wiring.</strong> Composite components
      split responsibilities across multiple tags (panel, trigger,
      controller, indicator) with reactive attribute binding between them
      through the composables layer.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Custom-element-aware directives.</strong> Click-outside and
      intersection observers handle both regular DOM and shadow DOM, using
      a single shared observer with a WeakMap of callbacks. Same pattern as
      DS-V1; refined for Vue 3.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="jm-rule" />

  <p class="project-foot">
    Back to <a href="/projects/design-system-v2">DS-V2 overview</a>
    &middot; Compare to <a href="/projects/design-system-v1/components">DS-V1 components</a>
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .project-back {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--jm-color-muted);
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    text-transform: lowercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .project-meta {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--jm-color-muted);
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .project-meta .project-year {
    color: var(--jm-color-fg);
  }

  .project-meta .project-status {
    color: var(--jm-color-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  .meta-sep {
    color: var(--jm-color-border);
  }

  .page-lede {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--jm-color-fg);
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--jm-color-accent);
    text-transform: lowercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .stack-list {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: max-content 1fr;
    gap: 0.4rem 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .stack-list dt {
    color: var(--jm-color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.78em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding-top: 0.15rem;
  }

  .stack-list dd {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--jm-color-fg);
    font-size: 0.95em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .stack-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.2rem;
    }
    .stack-list dd {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
  }

  .proof-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
  }

  .proof-list li {
    position: relative;
    margin: 0.6rem 0;
  }

  .proof-list li::before {
    content: ">";
    color: var(--jm-color-muted);
    position: absolute;
    left: -1.25rem;
  }

  .proof-list strong {
    color: var(--jm-color-fg);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  code {
    font-family: var(--jm-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: #1a1a1a;
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
  }

  .project-foot {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--jm-color-muted);
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
</style>
